  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">BEL/BELDOCS Special 2020&#x2013;I for Integrity</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In its thirteenth edition, International Documentary Film Festival Beldocs sets off for a deeper exploration into the value of pursuing the truth in the public interest. I for Integrity is a collaborative and impactful platform aimed at consolidating professional and wider audiences by the means of auteur filmmaking in the field between research-based, investigative journalism, activism and cinema. Through its activities, the project addresses the urgent problems arising from the existing societal context, including the limited reach of investigative journalism agenda, endangered state of local media, lack of media literacy and the need for young people to engage more in public-interest journalism and to nurture values of professional integrity. The core project activities that will take place during the Beldocs festival (3-10 September, 2020) will be based on the documentary program in the exciting intersection between filmmaking and investigative journalism, and will create a new, creative experience for presenting investigative journalism to the public. At the same time, audiences will explore various connections with filmmakers, journalists, activists and the real people behind the most riveting stories committed to film.</narrative>
  </description>
